SUMMARY:IN PERSON: BIPOC & Beloveds Shabbat
DESCRIPTION:BIPOC Shabbat – Beloved community\, this space is for Black\, Brown and Indigenous folks\, and folks who identify as People of Color AND their Beloveds!! Join us as we slow down\, embody self-care and step fully into our time of rest. We’ll gather at 6:45 and at 7pm we will light candles and invoke sacred space together in a brief service. Please bring a potluck dish to share.  \nThis space is for us\, created by us. Please contact the BIPOC Council at bipoc@kehillasynagogue.org if you have any questions\, want to RSVP to attend or you would like to co-lead\, lead\, or create.  \n  \nFor in-person attendance\, please adhere to the COVID Public Health Protocols: \nKehilla requires masking at all in-person\, indoor events. See the full Kehilla COVID Public Health Protocols here\, and see other accessibility information here. \nAll events at Kehilla are scent-free. Click here for information about what it means to be scent-free. \n  \nSee a more detailed accessibility description of Kehilla on our website here.
URL:https://kehillasynagogue.org/event/in-person-bipoc-beloveds-shabbat-2-2-2-2/2026-03-13/
LOCATION:Kehilla Community Synagogue\, 1300 Grand Avenue\, Piedmont\, CA\, 94610\, United States
CATEGORIES:Feature on Home Page,Services
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://kehillasynagogue.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/kabbalat-shabbat.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Unnamed Organizer":MAILTO:info@kehillasynagogue.org
END:VEVENT
