SUMMARY:Volunteer Opportunity - In-Person: Sacred Land Committee Hands On Gardening
DESCRIPTION:Avodah/Volunteer hours opportunity: \nThe Sacred Land Committee is dedicated to honoring the heritage of the Lisjan Ohlone people and our own Jewish heritage. We are seeking to bring the unceded land (called Huchiun) of the Lisjan Ohlone people\, on which Kehilla rests\, into harmony with Indigenous and Jewish values. We will be refurbishing the outside spaces (like the courtyard\, and front and back gardens) and reconnecting with the land and its spirit. If you enjoy gardening with a vision of environmental  integrity you are encouraged to join us. \nFor more information\, or to let us know you’re coming\, please contact us at: infoslc@kehillasynagogue.org \n 
URL:https://kehillasynagogue.org/event/volunteer-opportunity-in-person-sacred-land-committee-hands-on-gardening/2026-03-20/
CATEGORIES:Feature on Home Page
END:VEVENT
