SUMMARY:ONLINE ONLY: Shabbat Morning - Tzav - NEW TIME -
DESCRIPTION:Shabbat Morning – Tzav \nThe service is starting earlier [9:45] than most services to allow people time to get to No Kings Day protests. \nJoin us for a celebratory online only Shabbat morning service with Rabbi David Cooper\, and Beth Dickinson\, exploring parashat Tzav. In Leviticus 7:11-15 the Torah describes a sacrifice called Shelamim sometimes translated as the “well-being” sacrifice but it may be better understood as the “make-whole” offering. We’ll consider how that may apply this day as we prepare to protest how this administration is a source of brokenness in so many ways. \nJOIN US HERE  \nKehilla requires masking at all in-person\, indoor events\, except youth B’mitzvah ceremonies (mask-optional b’mitzvah ceremonies will be noted as such in the event title). See the full Kehilla COVID-19 Safety Protocols here\, and see other accessibility information here. \nAll events at Kehilla are scent-free. Click here for information about what it means to be scent-free.
URL:https://kehillasynagogue.org/event/multi-access-shabbat-morning-39-5-49/
CATEGORIES:Feature on Home Page,Services
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://kehillasynagogue.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Untitled-design-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
